---
---

<section class="py-24 px-6 bg-white/50 dark:bg-black/20">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">The problem</p>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">
        The EU AI Act requires traceability.<br />
        Your tools weren't built for this.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/50">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold mb-3">Splunk gives you logs, not audit trails</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Your engineering team uses observability tools for debugging. But a raw timestamp and a JSON blob is not what an EU regulator will accept as proof of compliance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/50">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold mb-3">OneTrust charges €50K+ for features you don't need</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Enterprise GRC platforms are built for risk assessments and vendor management — not for tracking what your AI agents decided. You're paying for a data center when all you need is a receipt.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/50">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold mb-3">Nobody knows what their AI actually did</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          The scariest sentence in AI compliance: "I don't know why it made that decision." Without cryptographic receipts, you have no proof — just logs that can be edited, deleted, or denied.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 text-sm">
        You're caught between the sword of regulation and the wall of budget.<br />
        AgentTrail is the way out.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
